+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DSJT736Gx1BNaPnU6cHPf3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# T3: Full-Text Search Feature\n     2→\n     3→## Category\n     4→features/medium\n     5→\n     6→## Timeout\n     7→30 minutes\n     8→\n     9→## Description\n    10→An existing Express + SQLite note-taking API has CRUD endpoints for notes (title, body, tags, timestamps) and tag-based filtering. Add full-text search using SQLite FTS5.\n    11→\n    12→## Requirements\n    13→\n    14→### 1. Search Endpoint: `GET /notes/search?q=<query>`\n    15→- Full-text search across note titles and bodies using SQLite FTS5\n    16→- Results ranked by relevance (BM25 ranking)\n    17→- Snippet highlighting with `<mark>` tags around matched terms\n    18→- Quoted phrase support (e.g., `?q=\"exact phrase\"`)\n    19→- Pagination: 20 results per page, controlled by `?page=N` parameter\n    20→- Response format: `{ results: SearchResult[], total: number, page: number, perPage: number }`\n    21→- Returns 400 if `q` parameter is missing or empty\n    22→\n    23→### 2. Suggest Endpoint: `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>`\n    24→- Autocomplete that returns up to 5 matching note titles\n    25→- Matches prefix against note content (title and body)\n    26→- Response format: `{ results: SuggestResult[] }`\n    27→- Returns 400 if `q` parameter is missing or empty\n    28→\n    29→### 3. FTS Index Synchronization\n    30→- FTS index must stay in sync when notes are created, updated, or deleted\n    31→- Use SQLite triggers or manual sync in the CRUD operations\n    32→\n    33→## Interfaces (already defined in `src/models.ts`)\n    34→\n    35→```ts\n    36→interface SearchResult {\n    37→  id: number;\n    38→  title: string;\n    39→  snippet: string;  // with <mark> highlighting\n    40→  rank: number;\n    41→}\n    42→\n    43→interface SuggestResult {\n    44→  id: number;\n    45→  title: string;\n    46→}\n    47→```\n    48→\n    49→## Existing Code\n    50→- `src/db.ts` - Database setup with `notes` table\n    51→- `src/models.ts` - TypeScript interfaces (SearchResult and SuggestResult already defined)\n    52→- `src/routes.ts` - CRUD routes for notes\n    53→- `src/errors.ts` - Error handling middleware\n    54→- `src/server.ts` - Express app setup\n    55→- `src/seed.ts` - Seed script with ~50 sample notes\n    56→\n    57→## Tests\n    58→- `tests/notes.test.ts` - 15 existing CRUD tests (must continue passing)\n    59→- `tests/search.test.ts` - 20 search tests (must pass after implementation)\n    60→\n    61→## Validation\n    62→```bash\n    63→npm test\n    64→```\n    65→All 35 tests must pass.\n    66→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QSbw7e9f94gfJh1eyEjpoA","session_id":"45ca8bcf-ca6a-40c4-a2d8-afdeea6746e3","uuid":"ff6c51da-e0fa-4823-b69b-4ea7d1a0df1a"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QSbw7e9f94gfJh1eyEjpoA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete overview. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI have thoroughly explored the entire codebase. Here's a complete summary:\n\n### 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE\n\n**Files in workspace:**\n- `/workspace/package.json` - Dependencies and scripts\n- `/workspace/tsconfig.json` - TypeScript configuration\n- `/workspace/vitest.config.ts` - Vitest test configuration\n- `/workspace/TASK.md` - Task requirements\n- `/workspace/src/db.ts` - Database setup and initialization\n- `/workspace/src/models.ts` - TypeScript interfaces\n- `/workspace/src/routes.ts` - CRUD API routes\n- `/workspace/src/errors.ts` - Error handling classes and middleware\n- `/workspace/src/server.ts` - Express app factory\n- `/workspace/src/seed.ts` - Database seeding script\n- `/workspace/tests/notes.test.ts` - CRUD endpoint tests\n- `/workspace/tests/search.test.ts` - Full-text search endpoint tests\n\n---\n\n### 2. PACKAGE.JSON\n\n**Name:** bench-fts-search  \n**Version:** 1.0.0  \n**Type:** Module (ES modules)  \n\n**Dependencies:**\n- better-sqlite3 ^11.0.0 - SQLite database\n- express ^4.21.0 - Web framework\n\n**Dev Dependencies:**\n- typescript ^5.4.0\n- vitest ^2.0.0 - Test runner\n- eslint ^8.56.0\n- @typescript-eslint/parser ^7.0.0\n- @typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin ^7.0.0\n- @types/better-sqlite3 ^7.6.0\n- @types/express ^4.17.0\n- supertest ^7.0.0 - HTTP assertions\n- @types/supertest ^6.0.0\n- tsx ^4.0.0 - TypeScript executor\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `npm run build` → tsc (compile TypeScript)\n- `npm run lint` → eslint src/ tests/\n- `npm test` → vitest run (run all tests)\n- `npm run seed` → tsx src/seed.ts (seed database)\n\n---\n\n### 3. DATABASE SETUP (src/db.ts)\n\n**Function: `createDatabase(path?: string)`**\n- Creates SQLite database at specified path or in-memory (`:memory:`)\n- Enables WAL (Write-Ahead Logging) pragma\n- Enables foreign key constraints\n- Creates `notes` table with columns:\n  - `id` - INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT\n  - `title` - TEXT NOT NULL\n  - `body` - TEXT NOT NULL\n  - `tags` - TEXT DEFAULT '[]' (JSON array as string)\n  - `created_at` - TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n  - `updated_at` - TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n\n**Function: `seedDatabase(db: Database.Database)`**\n- Inserts 45 sample notes into the database\n- Uses transaction for batch insertion\n- Sample notes cover topics: programming, cooking, travel, science, music, etc.\n\n**Sample seed notes include:**\n- \"Getting Started with TypeScript\"\n- \"Introduction to Python Programming\"\n- \"Understanding Database Indexing\"\n- \"Homemade Pasta Recipe\"\n- \"Classic Chocolate Chip Cookies\"\n- \"Travel Guide: Tokyo Japan\"\n- \"Exploring Paris France\"\n- \"Quantum Computing Basics\"\n- And 37 more covering diverse topics\n\n---\n\n### 4. MODELS (src/models.ts)\n\n**Interface: `Note`**\n```typescript\n{\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string; // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Interface: `NoteInput`**\n```typescript\n{\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[]; // Optional array of tag strings\n}\n```\n\n**Interface: `SearchResult`**\n```typescript\n{\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string; // with <mark> highlighting\n  rank: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Interface: `SuggestResult`**\n```typescript\n{\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. ROUTES (src/routes.ts)\n\n**Function: `createRoutes(db: Database.Database): Router`**\n\n**CRUD Endpoints:**\n\n1. **GET /notes** - List all notes with optional tag filtering\n   - Query param: `?tag=tagname` (optional)\n   - Uses `json_each()` for tag filtering\n   - Returns notes sorted by created_at DESC\n   - Response: `{ notes: Note[] }`\n\n2. **GET /notes/:id** - Get single note by ID\n   - Returns 404 if note not found\n   - Response: `{ note: Note }`\n\n3. **POST /notes** - Create new note\n   - Required fields: title, body\n   - Optional: tags (array)\n   - Tags stored as JSON string\n   - Returns 201 with created note\n   - Returns 400 if title or body is missing/empty\n   - Response: `{ note: Note }`\n\n4. **PUT /notes/:id** - Update note\n   - Allows partial updates (only update provided fields)\n   - Updates `updated_at` timestamp\n   - Returns 404 if note not found\n   - Response: `{ note: Note }`\n\n5. **DELETE /notes/:id** - Delete note\n   - Returns 204 No Content on success\n   - Returns 404 if note not found\n\nAll routes have try-catch with error handling passed to next() middleware.\n\n---\n\n### 6. ERROR HANDLING (src/errors.ts)\n\n**Custom Error Classes:**\n\n1. **NotFoundError**\n   - Extends Error\n   - statusCode: 404\n   - Default message: \"Resource not found\"\n\n2. **ValidationError**\n   - Extends Error\n   - statusCode: 400\n   - Default message: \"Validation failed\"\n\n**Function: `errorHandler(err, _req, res, _next)`**\n- Express error middleware that handles both error types\n- Returns JSON response with error message\n- Unknown errors return 500 with \"Internal server error\"\n- Logs unknown errors to console\n\n---\n\n### 7. SERVER SETUP (src/server.ts)\n\n**Interface: `App`**\n```typescript\n{\n  app: express.Express;\n  db: Database.Database;\n}\n```\n\n**Function: `createApp(dbPath?: string): App`**\n- Creates database (in-memory if no path)\n- Initializes Express app\n- Adds JSON middleware\n- Mounts CRUD routes\n- Adds error handler middleware\n\n**Function: `createSeededApp(dbPath?: string): App`**\n- Calls `createApp()`\n- Seeds the database with 45 sample notes\n- Returns app and db instance\n\n**Server startup logic:**\n- If run directly (as main module):\n  - Creates seeded app\n  - Reads PORT from env or defaults to 3000\n  - Logs startup message\n\n---\n\n### 8. SEED SCRIPT (src/seed.ts)\n\n- Takes optional database path from command line argument (defaults to 'notes.db')\n- Creates database\n- Seeds it with 45 sample notes\n- Reports count of seeded notes\n- Closes database connection\n\n---\n\n### 9. TEST FILES\n\n#### notes.test.ts (15 CRUD tests)\n\nTests the basic CRUD operations:\n1. GET /notes returns all notes\n2. GET /notes/:id returns specific note\n3. GET /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n4. POST /notes creates note with title and body\n5. POST /notes creates note with tags\n6. POST /notes returns 400 without title\n7. POST /notes returns 400 without body\n8. PUT /notes/:id updates note\n9. PUT /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n10. DELETE /notes/:id removes note\n11. DELETE /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n12. GET /notes?tag=X filters by tag\n13. Notes have created_at timestamp\n14. Notes have updated_at timestamp\n15. PUT updates updated_at timestamp\n\nUses:\n- Vitest describe/it/expect\n- Supertest for HTTP assertions\n- Creates fresh in-memory database for each test\n- Uses beforeEach/afterEach for setup/teardown\n\n#### search.test.ts (20 Full-Text Search tests)\n\nTests the search functionality to be implemented:\n1. GET /notes/search?q=keyword returns matching notes\n2. Results have snippet field with <mark> tags\n3. Snippets contain <mark> tags around matched terms\n4. Results ranked by relevance (ascending rank order)\n5. Exact phrase search support: ?q=\"exact phrase\"\n6. Search returns id, title, snippet, rank fields\n7. GET /notes/search?q=nonexistent returns empty array\n8. GET /notes/search without q returns 400\n9. GET /notes/search?q= (empty) returns 400\n10. Pagination: page=1 returns first 20 results\n11. Pagination: page=2 returns next results\n12. Pagination response includes total count\n13. GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix returns up to 5 titles\n14. Suggest results match prefix in title\n15. GET /notes/search/suggest?q= returns 400\n16. FTS syncs on create - new note appears in search\n17. FTS syncs on update - updated content appears in search\n18. FTS syncs on delete - deleted note disappears from search\n19. Special characters in query don't crash\n20. Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset\n\n**Expected response formats:**\n- Search: `{ results: SearchResult[], total: number, page: number, perPage: number }`\n- Suggest: `{ results: SuggestResult[] }`\n\n---\n\n### 10. CONFIGURATION FILES\n\n**tsconfig.json:**\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16\n- Strict mode enabled\n- esModuleInterop, skipLibCheck, forceConsistentCasingInFileNames enabled\n- Includes source maps and declaration files\n- Includes src/**, excludes node_modules, dist, tests\n\n**vitest.config.ts:**\n- Globals enabled\n- Test timeout: 10000ms\n\n---\n\n## SUMMARY\n\nThis is a TypeScript/Express/SQLite note-taking API with the following characteristics:\n\n**Current State:**\n- Fully functional CRUD API for notes\n- Tag-based filtering\n- Timestamp tracking\n- Error handling middleware\n- 45 seed notes for testing\n- 15 passing CRUD tests\n\n**What's Missing (Task Requirements):**\nThe project needs full-text search implementation with:\n1. FTS5 search endpoint supporting relevance ranking and snippets with highlighting\n2. Autocomplete suggest endpoint\n3. FTS index synchronization on CRUD operations\n4. Pagination support\n5. 20 additional tests that must pass\n\nThe search functionality needs to be added to make all 35 tests pass (15 existing CRUD + 20 new search tests)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a270e30 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 31935\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 33546</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"45ca8bcf-ca6a-40c4-a2d8-afdeea6746e3","uuid":"9eae4287-c7b1-4175-b73b-0b76330a6242","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The project structure (all files)\n2. The database setup in src/db.ts\n3. The models in src/models.ts\n4. The routes in sr